display_asset.caption: A new species of tortoise was identified on Santa Cruz, in the center of the Galápagos Islands.

summaries.body: For the first time in more than a century, scientists have identified a new species of Galápagos tortoise, the grand giants of the Pacific archipelago that helped inspire Darwin’s theory of evolution.

display_asset.caption: Mayor Kevin Johnson after the Sacramento Kings beat the Utah Jazz in Sacramento in 2012.

summaries.body: Kevin Johnson, the Sacramento mayor, said he would not seek re-election after the release of a videotaped police interview with a teenager who said he sexually abused her.

display_asset.caption: The Hendo Hoverboard uses magnetic field architecture technology along with a copper surface to create the effect of levitation at the Hendo Hover office in Los Gatos, Calif., last year.
display_asset.credit: Jason Henry for The New York Times

summaries.body: "Back to the Future" promised us hoverboards. But the movie that planted the dream might also be to blame for the lack of a futuristic and really fun transportation device.
Children who regularly use antibiotics gain weight faster than those who have never taken the drugs, according to new research.

display_asset.caption: PewDiePie is a Swedish YouTube star whose real name is Felix Kjellberg.

summaries.body: YouTube and its parent company, Google, are hoping users will be willing to pay to watch videos without ads. It also announced YouTube Originals, a slate of programming.

display_asset.caption: Carl Icahn, center, at an event in New York last month.
display_asset.credit: Stephen Yang for The New York Times

summaries.body: Carl Icahn, the billionaire businessman supporting Donald J. Trump for president, is starting a “super PAC” with an “initial commitment of $150 million” that will focus on corporate tax reform.

display_asset.caption: South African students tried to force their way through the gates of Parliament on Wednesday during clashes with the police in Cape Town.

summaries.body: Riot police clashed with students protesting tuition increases in Cape Town, in the latest in a series of student demonstrations that have gripped South Africa.

display_asset.caption: Chris Rock during the Hollywood Film Awards in  2014.

summaries.body: One problem solved for next year’s Oscar broadcast: Chris Rock, a proven audience draw, will return to host the Academy Awards ceremony, set for Feb. 28.
On social media, Disney princesses are often reimagined as hipsters, celebrities and political refugees. An artist explains why the characters are ripe for reinvention.

display_asset.caption: In an image from a Reuters video, an empty red pickup truck was seen parked on the side of the road as police searched the area.

summaries.body: The Albuquerque police are searching for a person suspected of killing a 4-year-old girl in a road rage confrontation.

display_asset.credit: Bruce Newman/The Oxford Eagle, via Associated Press

summaries.body: The University of Mississippi student senate voted Tuesday night for the removal of the state flag — which contains the Confederate battle flag — from university grounds. Such a decision would be up to the administration.

display_asset.caption: Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont and Hillary Rodham Clinton at the Democratic presidential debate in Las Vegas last week.

summaries.body: Hillary Rodham Clinton is seeing a post-debate bounce with New Hampshire Democrats. A poll shows 38 percent of likely voters supporting her, ahead of Senator Bernie Sanders.
A U.S. Navy F/A-18 Hornet, like the one above, crashed in England on Wednesday. The local police said the pilot had died.

display_asset.caption: The "21" Club jockeys, freshly painted, standing in formation in the studio of the artist Andrew Tedesco.
display_asset.credit: Hilary Swift for The New York Times

summaries.body: When three dozen iron lawn jockeys outside Manhattan's storied “21” Club vanished, some locals were concerned. But they were getting their first refurbishment in 85 years.
Ahmed Mohamed, the Texas teenager who was detained for bringing a homemade clock to school, is moving to Qatar after winning a scholarship to a science program.

display_asset.caption: John Boyega and Daisy Ridley in the “Star Wars: The Force Awakens” trailer that had its premiere on Monday night.

summaries.body: Fandango and AMC were, for a time, overwhelmed by online demand for tickets to the latest installment of the “Star Wars" saga, "The Force Awakens,” which opens Dec. 18.
Yahoo reported disappointing third-quarter financial results and said it would soon begin to use Google to power some of its search results and advertising.
Taylor Swift’s “Blank Space” has become the most-watched video on the music platform Vevo, surpassing Justin Bieber’s “Baby,” with more than 1.2 billion views.

display_asset.caption: Members of the Afghan security forces in front of a vehicle that was set on fire after fighting between government forces and Taliban militants in Ghazni last week. In addition to seizing Ghormach District in the northwest just days ago, the Taliban have been attacking other parts of the country, including the province of Ghazni.

summaries.body: The Taliban killed at least 22 policemen and captured a district security chief along with many of his men in the northwestern Afghan province of Faryab.

display_asset.caption: The Crédit Agricole case signals the final chapter of a long-running investigation into sanctions violations across the banking industry.

summaries.body: Crédit Agricole agreed to pay a $787 million penalty over accusations that it transferred billions of dollars on behalf of Iran and other nations in violation of U.S. sanctions.

display_asset.caption: A gathering in memory of Corey Jones was held at Bible Church of God in Boynton Beach, Fla., on Monday. The 31-year-old drummer for the church was killed by a police officer in Palm Beach Gardens.
display_asset.credit: Bruce R. Bennett/The Palm Beach Post

summaries.body: The shooting of Corey Jones, a Florida drummer, is the latest killing of an African-American at the hands of the police. The Palm Beach County sheriff's department is investigating.

display_asset.credit: An image from NBC4 (Los Angelens) video

summaries.body: Mayor Eric Garcetti's first "town hall" for residents of South Los Angeles ended early and abruptly after Black Lives Matter protesters disrupted it.

display_asset.caption: Conservative Japanese lawmakers, left, visiting the Yasukuni Shrine on Tuesday. The shrine commemorates Japan’s war dead, including war criminals.

summaries.body: Japanese legislators visited on Tuesday the contentious Yasukuni Shrine, where the country's war dead, including war criminals, are buried. The prime minister stayed away.
A five-alarm fire engulfed a building in Chelsea in downtown Manhattan early Tuesday morning, forcing the evacuation of surrounding buildings.
A fight between two passengers, apparently over a reclined seat, forced a San Francisco-bound Southwest Airlines flight to make an emergency landing in Los Angeles.
Laser blasts, droids and Darth Vader's cracked helmet were part of a trailer for “Star Wars: The Force Awakens” that was unveiled on "Monday Night Football." It opens Dec. 18.
Christopher Leonard, 17, who was beaten in a New York church, plans to testify against at least one attacker, the authorities said. His brother, 19, was killed in the attack.

display_asset.caption: Carolyn Tousignant with a photo of her daughter Carrie Ann Jopek, who was killed in 1982. Mr. Ferreira, a neighbor, has been charged in her death.

summaries.body: A man has confessed to the 1982 killing of a 13-year-old Milwaukee girl, law enforcement officials said. He was 16 at the time and lived down the street from her.

display_asset.caption: HealthCare.gov during the open enrollment period last fall. One of the website's new tools this fall will allow consumers to search health plans in their area for a specific doctor or hospital.

summaries.body: Federal officials and insurers were blaming each other for problems on HealthCare.gov, which technology teams were racing to fix before the enrollment period starts Nov. 1.

display_asset.caption: The signature structure of the Rockaways, the boardwalk, is only partially rebuilt, though the entire length is expected to reopen by next summer.
display_asset.credit: Christian Hansen for The New York Times

summaries.body: A new documentary about Hurricane Sandy, “Everything Is Different Now: Rockaway After the Storm,” was shot mostly a year later, in the midst of a broad rebuilding effort.
